                    <h3 class="hny-title">
                        SGO Farming Project
                    </h3>
                </div>
                <p class="mt-3">
                        On the 29th of August 2022, we had launched our trial period of planting with 100 seedlings of cabbage, cauliflower, lettuce, broccoli, spinach and brinjal (eggplant). Within 4 weeks, we have seen bountiful success in our work. It was such a joy to see our vegetables flourishing.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-3">
                    It certainly was an encouraging indication that we should continue this journey in making our Mission sustainable. This step of faith will not only be the beginning of our farming sector but it will also ensure that we are not affected by the fluctuating food prices, and any food shortages.
                        We are so blessed and grateful for the various people, who had played a role in this faith stirring project, whether it was by their sponsoring of seeds, seedlings, voluntary labour and prayers. 
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-3">
                        Due to the amazing success of this endeavor we had decided to expand this vision to reach out, to not only our communities but throughout KZN.
                        Amidst this amazing project, we had our very first intake of an Agricultural in-service trainee on the 4th September, 2023. Our goal is to mobilize God’s people for service. The opportunities are here now to join us in the harvest. We’re looking for people to come work with us here in South Africa.
                    </p> 
